The paper deals with authentication protocols and cryptography, which are typically categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of a semi-trusted computer and the focus on designing authentication protocols that can be executed by humans suggest that the paper may also fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also involves the use of functions that are easy for humans to evaluate, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of password schemes, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
